# Trivy IaC finding suppressions for the development docker-compose stack.
# These findings are intentional in the dev environment and do not apply to
# production (K3s/RKE2 deployments use SecurityContexts + non-root images).

# DS002: Container should not run as root.
# Dev compose intentionally uses vendor-default users; production Helm charts
# set securityContext.runAsNonRoot=true and specific runAsUser per service.
DS002

# DS026 / DS027: No CPU/memory limits set.
# Resource limits are enforced by K3s LimitRanges in staging/prod. The dev
# stack runs on a single workstation where limits cause unnecessary friction.
DS026
DS027
